  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence was gathered from bench-top PIV measurements and in-vitro hemolysis testing; a summary claim capturing the overall adequacy of the model is included. Note: the claim node is provided as a structured assertion; supporting derivation linkage is recorded in the project evidence archive.",
